---
// /about — NEW conversion-focused guide/trust page (supporting-pages-spec.md).
// NOT a resume. Reader-first: "why would this time be different?" Copy assembled
// from Jon's own language (voice.md verbatim phrases). Jon is the expert GUIDE,
// never a personal recovery story; never imply he smoked. Customer is the hero.
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import SiteHeader from '../components/SiteHeader.astro';
import SiteFooter from '../components/SiteFooter.astro';
import '../styles/home.css';

// $97 session sells via the standalone landing page (decided 2026-07-12).
const SESSION_URL = 'https://abq-landing-v2.vercel.app';
---

<Base
  title="About Jon Fritsch — Always Be Quitting"
  description="You don't lack willpower — you lack the right support. Meet Jon, a certified tobacco treatment specialist who has spent 25 years helping people quit smoking and vaping for the last time."
>
  <SiteHeader />

  <!-- 1 · reader-first hero -->
  <header class="band band--mist hero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="kicker">About Always Be Quitting</p>
      <h1 class="display-xl hl" style="margin-top:1.2rem">
        You're not weak, and you're not out of chances. You just haven't had the <em>right guide.</em>
      </h1>
      <p class="hero__sub">
        If you've tried to quit smoking or vaping before and it didn't stick, that isn't the end of your story.
        It's the reason to try again — this time with someone in your corner who does this all day, every day.
      </p>
      <p class="trust">CTTS &amp; NCNTT certified · 25 years helping people quit · Customer is the hero — I'm just the guide</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- 2 · the guide (empathy → expertise → origin insight) -->
  <section class="band band--white guide">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="guide__row reveal">
        <div class="guide__photo">[ Jon — real photo coming ]</div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="display-lg">I'm Jon, and I've helped people who were sure they'd never quit — quit for life.</h2>
          <p style="margin-top:1.2rem; color:var(--soft)">
            I understand how discouraging this struggle is. For 25 years I've helped all kinds of people stop
            smoking and vaping, and <em>I can help you, too.</em>
          </p>
          <p style="color:var(--soft)">
            For decades I taught health workshops and trained future doctors and nurses about tobacco treatment.
            Somewhere along the way I learned the thing that changed how I work: none of the science matters if the
            person in front of you never actually does anything to change. The hardest part of quitting isn't the
            nicotine. <strong style="color:var(--ink)">It's starting.</strong> So that's where I put my energy now —
            helping real people take the first action, and every action after it.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 3 · why this time can be different (the philosophy, in Jon's words) -->
  <section class="band band--paper recognition">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="lead reveal">
        <p class="kicker">Why this time can be different</p>
        <h2 class="display-lg hl">It was never about willpower. It was about <em>the right support.</em></h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid grid--2">
        <div class="card reveal">
          <h3>You don't have to be ready.</h3>
          <p>
            The most important question in quitting isn't <em>how</em> — it's <em>when</em>. My answer is always the
            same: now. You don't need all the answers. You just have to take action, and I'll help you take it.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card reveal">
          <h3>Temporary abstinence isn't quitting.</h3>
          <p>
            Stopping for a few weeks and quitting for life are two different things — and the second one is the whole
            game. Transformation is the real work, and it's exactly the part most people are never supported through.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card reveal">
          <h3>If you've relapsed, you're the norm.</h3>
          <p>
            You're not broken and you didn't fail. Most people who quit for good went back several times first.
            Welcome to the 97% club — it's where permanent quitters come from, not the people who don't make it.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card reveal">
          <h3>No gimmicks. No willpower mythology.</h3>
          <p>
            No crystals, no mushrooms, no white-knuckle lectures. Just proven, evidence-based approaches shaped
            around your life — from someone who genuinely likes helping people through this.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 4 · anti-brag credentials -->
  <section class="band band--teal transform">
    <div class="wrap reveal">
      <p class="kicker">The part where I'd normally brag</p>
      <h2 class="display-lg" style="margin-top:1rem">
        I could spend this whole page listing credentials. <span class="sweep"><em>I won't.</em></span>
      </h2>
      <p>
        You should know I'm qualified, so here it is once: I'm a Certified Tobacco Treatment Specialist, NCNTT
        certified, I've taught tobacco treatment to university health classes since 2011, and I've spent decades
        building programs that actually change behavior. That's the last you'll hear about it — you're not here for
        my résumé. You're here to quit.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 5 · proof -->
  <section class="band band--white proof">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="kicker">Real people, done smoking or vaping</p>
      <div class="grid grid--3" style="margin-top:2rem">
        <figure class="card quote reveal">
          <blockquote>Jon became my outlet, a safe person who helped me negotiate that struggle. The impact he has had on my life is transformative.</blockquote>
          <figcaption><b>Katherine R.</b> · One Year Vape Free</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="card quote reveal">
          <blockquote>He broke the all-or-nothing thinking for me. He came in with curiosity, just getting to understand where I was at, so that he could help me.</blockquote>
          <figcaption><b>Kait</b> · 9 Years Sober, Now Smoke-Free</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="card quote reveal">
          <blockquote>I've invited Jon to teach about tobacco treatment to my university class for 9 straight semesters… informative, entertaining and inspiring.</blockquote>
          <figcaption><b>Ashley Foster, MPH, RD, CHES</b> · University Professor</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 6 · CTA: two doors -->
  <section class="band band--paper band--dots doors">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2 class="display-lg hl">Ready when you are. <em>Pick your path.</em></h2>
      <div class="grid grid--2">
        <div class="door door--community reveal">
          <h3>The ABQ Community</h3>
          <p>Weekly live Q&amp;A calls with Jon and 24/7 access to a community of people quitting alongside you. Move forward at your own pace, with support and accountability the whole way. You don't even have to be ready to quit to start.</p>
          <div class="price">$97/month</div>
          <p class="door__terms">3-month commitment, then just $47/month.</p>
          <a class="btn btn--cta" href="/community">Join the Community</a>
        </div>
        <div class="door door--session reveal">
          <h3>1:1 Coaching: A Special Session</h3>
          <p>Schedule a personal conversation and get yourself moving forward. Whether you can't seem to start, you're slipping, or you've relapsed and want to try again — this is where we begin. A focused 50-minute session with a specialist who's spent 25 years helping people quit for the last time.</p>
          <div class="price">$97 one-time</div>
          <a class="btn btn--cta" href={SESSION_URL}>Book your $97 session</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="doors__mitigate reveal">$97 is less than most people spend in a single month on smoking or vaping.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 7 · soft on-ramp: free guide opt-in -->
  <section class="band band--white" style="padding-block: clamp(3.5rem, 7vw, 5.5rem)">
    <div class="wrap" style="max-width:640px">
      <div class="optin reveal">
        <h3>Want to start in the next 20 minutes?</h3>
        <p><em>Grab the free Always Be Quitting "Quick-Start Guide" and begin breaking the addiction today — you don't have to be ready to quit to start.</em></p>
        <form action="/api/subscribe" method="post">
          <input type="email" name="email" placeholder="Your email" required />
          <button class="btn btn--cta" type="submit">Send me the free guide</button>
        </form>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 8 · tagline close -->
  <section class="band band--navy final">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2 class="display-xl hl">Always be quitting, <em>until you've quit for the last time.</em></h2>
    </div>
  </section>

  <SiteFooter />
</Base>
